2002-02-18 17:25  Guus Sliepen <guus@sliepen.warande.net>

	* doc/tinc.conf.5, doc/tinc.texi, po/POTFILES.in, po/nl.po,
	src/Makefile.am, src/conf.c, src/conf.h, src/connection.c,
	src/connection.h, src/edge.c, src/edge.h, src/graph.c, src/meta.c,
	src/net.c, src/net.h, src/net_packet.c, src/net_setup.c,
	src/net_socket.c, src/netutl.c, src/netutl.h, src/node.c,
	src/node.h, src/process.c, src/protocol_auth.c,
	src/protocol_edge.c, src/route.c, src/subnet.c, src/subnet.h,
	src/freebsd/device.c, src/linux/device.c, src/netbsd/device.c,
	src/openbsd/device.c, src/solaris/device.c: 
	- Non-blocking connect()s.  
	- Socket handling revamped to use sockaddr_t.  
	- tinc can now tunnel over IPv6.  
	- Handle all addresses and subnets in network byte order.  
	  Only convert them when they need to be printed.  
	- IPv6 subnets bigger than /128 now work.  
	- Use %s and strerror(errno) instead of %m.  

