2001-10-27 14:13  Guus Sliepen <guus@sliepen.warande.net>

	* src/: conf.c, conf.h, connection.c, connection.h, device.h,
	meta.c, net.c, net.h, netutl.c, netutl.h, node.c, node.h,
	process.c, protocol.c, protocol.h, route.c, route.h, subnet.c,
	subnet.h, tincd.c, vertex.c, vertex.h, linux/device.c: Big bad
	commit: 
	- Transition to new node/vertex/connection structures 
	- Use new configuration handling everywhere 
	- Linux tun/tap device handling cleanup 
	- Start of IPv6 support in route.c 
	
	It compiles, but it won't link.  

